body.text: The board is a 2D canvas with a physics engine. Gravity makes sprites fall and boundary makes them bounce.
Display the board. The game loop will start after leaving main.

U0I45lu5Yui66MmPusQWR5jW.text: Checks if user press LEFT, RIGHT or SHOOT buttons and responds accordingly

sOJOWDXk4uXFuw2EOnjqsUHM.text: Check if the user base hits the left hand side of the screen & stop it from going out

ZOIuaSXGzSGr4XA4WSkrEGv0.text: Check if the user base hits the right hand side of the screen and stop it from going out

xFAMHEfa72IJqrKzMjlA9F2S.text: Check if laser hits user controlled base and subtract a life if it does and reset the laser

OXmOE9QLoH524dBB5bHYRkLE.text: If rocket leaves the screen reset it

dP1MP2KQieXWjcvbd0gX5CW2.text: Check if alien laser hits the shields and remove the shield if it does

TEhPCtKynn4ZGHDdD3zCT304.text: Hide shield off screen and the remove it from the sprite set

BI7ofxUs0cS68o2WmSr6JTJi.text: If alien is above user base and laser is NOT currently being fired, then fire it

C5pQeTnFwuGAv8chnYrWkN4v.text: Check if Alien is hit by the rocket from the user base

xItV2gGnKg7muTmjAKYzKtN4.text: If all the aliens have been destroyed spawn a new wave of them

n5u7Xe0E7pypuhG2iqXdQjuH.text: This creates rows and columns of alien invaders

l0YbeFmEGt6l7Cv0abOqPdL8.text: This creates rows and columns of shields using rectangles

nZ0AAY1LwOSkbY8QzTFyNY4M.text: This function moves the aliens left and right and then down when they hit either side.

app.comment:
#pilvu2

I found a way to do a touch and hold event, but had to code it a different way as the touch sprite event doesn't allow for this at present. So you can now hold down the left and right buttons to move. I also added shields to make it a little easier on the first wave.
